The '''Bollin Exotic Animal Emporium''' was a [[Zoo/Legends|zoo]] in [[Bollin]] on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]]. It had an assortment of deadly creatures, including the only known captured [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] in the [[Cularin system/Legends|system]]. Despite its name as an emporium, it did not sell animals, it displayed them. Its most successful act involved the rancor. The owner, [[Hlisk Squin]], worked with two other trainers.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

The Emporium was used as a cover for Squin's smuggling operations, although Squin's employees did not know of of the zoo's extra activities. He acted a middle man between [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] in the [[Cularin asteroid belt|asteroid belt]] and buyers of their goods. In the days of [[Riboga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]], Squin was involved in [[Slavery/Legends|slave]] running, using animal pens to move the slaves. In addition, some of Squin's competitors disappeared, possibly given as food to the animals.<ref name="LFC" /> In [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], Riboga's successor [[Nirama]] made sure that a [[Gael Kinner|person who had killed one employee of his]] ended in the rancor's cage. This death was later covered by news anchor [[Vell Narot]] from [[CSN]].<ref name="POB">{{LivingForce|The Price of Business}}</ref>

